[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Exploring dynamic class access**\n\nI'm considering that while we can't directly access SCL, we might use a natural API to reach it. Could we get SCL from the thread context or during processing? Maybe writing a custom annotation processor loaded with Lombok could work. I realize Javac uses `ProcessorClassLoader` to load processors, but it's not what Lombok uses. Lombok seems to internally create SCL, and I'm trying to figure out if our source can invoke `lombok.Lombok` directly. It seems like that won't be possible.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0cb9747e518cac76016a23964a8ed481958878530df6bfee88\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqI5ZnZWpRJEHD5_hzLGPPay4o8p9MxHi8T0-RhJ7lMAD_tj_8XwL6W8dpvcZ1i4NOrAc7zR96NsDkFpC403mV7R4JDRjVgL5DcoKQyN5W3m-nLZ_k_j0qIwnnFpSoVxOgTfPntXyc28YIxVGy5BZDBij4MSDHL1OLOzNagtjTSVO-Q30D9vDYBwTVTkLPHUov7gcOxBUruSb7oic5KdeIk2Yr4T9JI4nCQ7wQI-GbhRoMPHjMS7kSipcP6WuVI-JWV6gc1RwSC-d1YZPuuzahtBGVK9y69AaVgfaKssLgRhPF8E9MHSnPAMAvHkFH_1niw0mUkNjMv6JFmRyIbnPlyAWqIRtkezONkBej5QgbRm0WlAQ7ORxenKOmp7TIGgAy9sAtDmFqZGxELRBYCdoCgvNIirVl2zeeh6bUn4Yr809YfDKrUI_7zY22uy3QghT_8jGBEt5Fv0GB3s4RFO6B72u3aZ_404WZ9k1La-juEyHOIM1SnYRsetyzkxImjcu5_aBQpnK8PELbfjZzeAAF-1DxmS3PhuRowC4tC73U5CTmq7oeFgbDEzD_rhsksznt-Qo524LMYiyuPEWBFR4M-j7f7YouAPTuV4xHpe4_wt-KjZEqNHRpN-lTjDcE3cmIV-gMBWcS1XvAbN2atQDrZCdIPYAxGNI5u__fWP5givhm6BcSk8O72XrmUauj9BwoigCn9hqBUan1eSG-fWi6z2r6xQovQ_qpZddDl1dw17p2XNcUCpn6ccQ2ggvRBvrKqkcb0M8LVvJ4Q2SVa2kXDn3TlA-IWorCtJbVVIvJ-VcllMga5JB9d7S1vHvAH-59FehzfddkTfnnobSf02BGDLGmTY5Hp0FNhAxImiEzhn6QwM7Z7KmpmFgisYJWFItJJCY5PdTyht3tGiysNlkuDyVv1_K2anCl3H9LUvQbd3EcqBQ0O3YfGI8UnVFZpSURDvGRy2tY_kJ-m1K9uI59bk9t7No8jw4S9IMoM-peoukUUSmVJS1-rOt7efxsWBlo9ULyUJScXakKfEgK4lQ_ngRH-8TeranqXhhXy3XGdLulDCb3al0nxuKjcl8HNcWMExKqoBMuv5nPu81zfMQ_EVSYXmPrBfv4jgF-AqzG9X4qlMOnYMZcBQHivLNAFnWJ8BlzZNhnm9EPTIEsGTPhUlO_A_4WMIWx7iWO6m1DCvaZORyWqsO62Kvl